cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.HC 

Reasoning: 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on the task of bed-making using mobile manipulator robots. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is also likely as the approach involves using depth images to locate pick points on fabric. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is relevant as the paper presents a supervised deep transfer learning approach for the task. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the approach involves training a model to learn pick points on fabric. 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is less likely but still possible as the paper compares the results of human supervision with those of the robot and the baseline.
